The last expression is implying that in general we have $r<0$, $r\in(-1,0)$ and also $n_{\chi}<0$, because $\rho^{{\rm BEC}}_{\chi}<\rho^{{\rm nor}}_{\chi}$. Clearly, imposing the condition $h(t_{{\rm cr}})=0$,
